WEBVTT



00:00:10.048 --> 00:00:13.216
Welcome to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church Podcast.

00:00:13.376 --> 00:00:17.440
Our mission is to develop fully devoted followers of Christ.

00:00:17.952 --> 00:00:25.696
Thanks for joining us on the podcast. On today's episode, we will have Justin Wester reading Psalm 140 as part of our Psalms Project journey.

00:00:29.920 --> 00:00:32.672
Today I'll be reading Psalm 140.

00:00:33.152 --> 00:00:35.744
Deliver me, O Lord, from evil men.

00:00:35.584 --> 00:00:38.144
Preserved me from violent men.

00:00:38.048 --> 00:00:42.432
Who plan evil things in their heart and stir up wars continually

00:00:42.528 --> 00:00:45.280
They make their tongues sharp as a serpent's.

00:00:45.184 --> 00:00:48.736
And under their lips is the venom of asps.

00:00:48.800 --> 00:00:51.712
Guard me, O Lord, from the hands of the wicked.

00:00:51.552 --> 00:00:54.144
Preserve me from violent men.

00:00:53.824 --> 00:00:56.320
Who have planned to trip up my feet.

00:00:56.320 --> 00:00:59.040
The arrogant have hidden the trap from me.

00:00:58.976 --> 00:01:01.728
And with cords they have spread a net.

00:01:01.888 --> 00:01:05.152
Beside the way they have set snares for me.

00:01:05.280 --> 00:01:08.384
I say to the Lord, you are my God.

00:01:08.352 --> 00:01:11.776
Give ear to the voice of my pleas for mercy, O Lord.

00:01:11.712 --> 00:01:13.952
O Lord, my Lord.

00:01:13.696 --> 00:01:16.000
The strength of my salvation

00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:18.624
You have covered my head in the day of battle.

00:01:18.688 --> 00:01:22.208
Grant not, O Lord, the desires of the wicked,

00:01:22.208 --> 00:01:24.832
Do not further their evil plot.

00:01:24.576 --> 00:01:26.464
Or they will be exalted.

00:01:26.880 --> 00:01:29.472
I will not be able to do anything against you, but I will do anything against

00:01:29.504 --> 00:01:32.576
Let the mischief of their lips overwhelm them.

00:01:32.640 --> 00:01:35.360
Let burning coals fall upon them.

00:01:35.360 --> 00:01:37.632
Let them be cast into fire.

00:01:37.440 --> 00:01:39.392
into Myrie Pitts.

00:01:39.136 --> 00:01:41.344
No more to rise.

00:01:41.536 --> 00:01:45.408
Let not the slanderer be established in the land.

00:01:45.440 --> 00:01:48.768
Let evil hunt down the violent man speedily.

00:01:48.800 --> 00:01:52.736
I know the Lord will maintain the cause of the afflicted.

00:01:52.576 --> 00:01:55.168
and will execute justice for the needy.

00:01:55.136 --> 00:01:59.104
"Surely the righteous shall give thanks to your name."

00:01:59.040 --> 00:02:02.432
The upright shall dwell in your presence.

00:02:02.656 --> 00:02:08.608
And just some questions to think on as you read this psalm, Psalm 140, this psalm.

00:02:08.480 --> 00:02:10.624
week and today

00:02:10.560 --> 00:02:15.456
The first one is this, what really ensnares you in your walk with God?

00:02:15.232 --> 00:02:18.720
Or what really keeps you from following the path

00:02:18.720 --> 00:02:21.440
That God has set for you.

00:02:21.696 --> 00:02:22.688
And

00:02:22.496 --> 00:02:24.448
As you pray to God,

00:02:24.320 --> 00:02:26.016
And ask him to help

00:02:25.792 --> 00:02:30.496
What is it specifically that you're asking God to do for you today?

00:02:38.240 --> 00:02:46.368
We hope this message was encouraging to you. If you would like this kind of content delivered directly to you, consider subscribing to our channel.

00:02:46.464 --> 00:02:55.904
If you'd like more information about our church, please visit us on the web at canopyroads.org. And thanks for listening to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.
